.TH wxListItem 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxListItem \- This class stores information about a \fIwxListCtrl\fR item or column.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fIwxListItem\fR is a class which contains information about:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Zero based item position; see \fIsetId/2\fR and \fIgetId/1\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Zero based column index; see \fIsetColumn/2\fR and \fIgetColumn/1\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
The label (or header for columns); see \fIsetText/2\fR and \fIgetText/1\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
The zero based index into an image list; see \fIgetImage/1\fR and \fIsetImage/2\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
Application defined data; see \fISetData()\fR (not implemented in wx) and \fIGetData()\fR (not implemented in wx).

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
For columns only: the width of the column; see \fIsetWidth/2\fR and \fIgetWidth/1\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
For columns only: the format of the column; one of \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_LEFT\fR, \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_RIGHT\fR, \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_CENTRE\fR. See \fIsetAlign/2\fR and \fIgetAlign/1\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
The state of the item; see \fIsetState/2\fR and \fIgetState/1\fR. This is a bitlist of the following flags:

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_STATE_FOCUSED:\fR The item has the focus.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_STATE_SELECTED:\fR The item is selected.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_STATE_DONTCARE:\fR No special flags (the value of this constant is 0).

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_STATE_DROPHILITED:\fR The item is highlighted to receive a drop event. Win32 only.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_STATE_CUT:\fR The item is in the cut state. Win32 only.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
mask indicating which state flags are valid; this is a bitlist of the flags reported above for the item state. See \fIsetStateMask/2\fR and GetStateMask().

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
mask indicating which fields of this class are valid; see \fIsetMask/2\fR and \fIgetMask/1\fR. This is a bitlist of the following flags:

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_STATE:\fR The state field is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_TEXT:\fR The label field is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_IMAGE:\fR The image field is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_DATA:\fR The application-defined data field is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_WIDTH:\fR The column width field is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxLIST_MASK_FORMAT:\fR The column format field is valid.

.RE

.PP
The \fIwxListItem\fR object can also contain item-specific colour and font information: for this you need to call one of \fIsetTextColour/2\fR, \fIsetBackgroundColour/2\fR or \fIsetFont/2\fR functions on it passing it the colour/font to use. If the colour/font is not specified, the default list control colour/font is used.

.PP
See: \fIwxListCtrl\fR

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxListItem

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxListItem() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBclear(This) -> ok when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Resets the item state to the default.


.RE
.B
\fBdestroy(This :: wxListItem()) -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Destroys the object


.RE
.B
\fBgetAlign(This) -> wx:wx_enum() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the alignment for this item.

.PP
Can be one of \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_LEFT\fR, \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_RIGHT\fR or \fIwxLIST_FORMAT_CENTRE\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBgetBackgroundColour(This) -> wx:wx_colour4()\fR
\fB                             when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the background colour for this item.


.RE
.B
\fBgetColumn(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the zero-based column; meaningful only in report mode.


.RE
.B
\fBgetFont(This) -> wxFont:wxFont() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the font used to display the item.


.RE
.B
\fBgetId(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the zero-based item position.


.RE
.B
\fBgetImage(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the zero-based index of the image associated with the item into the image list.


.RE
.B
\fBgetMask(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns a bit mask indicating which fields of the structure are valid.

.PP
Can be any combination of the following values:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_STATE: \fIGetState\fR is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_TEXT: \fIGetText\fR is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_IMAGE: \fIGetImage\fR is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_DATA: \fIGetData\fR is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_WIDTH: \fIGetWidth\fR is valid.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_MASK_FORMAT: \fIGetFormat\fR is valid.

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBgetState(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns a bit field representing the state of the item.

.PP
Can be any combination of:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_STATE_DONTCARE: No special flags (the values of this constant is 0).

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_STATE_DROPHILITED: The item is highlighted to receive a drop event. Win32 only.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_STATE_FOCUSED: The item has the focus.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_STATE_SELECTED: The item is selected.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
wxLIST_STATE_CUT: The item is in the cut state. Win32 only.

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBgetText(This) -> unicode:charlist() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the label/header text.


.RE
.B
\fBgetTextColour(This) -> wx:wx_colour4() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the text colour.


.RE
.B
\fBgetWidth(This) -> integer() when This :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Meaningful only for column headers in report mode.

.PP
Returns the column width.


.RE
.B
\fBnew() -> wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Constructor.


.RE
.B
\fBnew(Item) -> wxListItem() when Item :: wxListItem().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBsetAlign(This, Align) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxListItem(), Align :: wx:wx_enum().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the alignment for the item.

.PP
See also \fIgetAlign/1\fR


.RE
.B
\fBsetBackgroundColour(This, ColBack) -> ok\fR
\fB                             when\fR
\fB                                 This :: wxListItem(),\fR
\fB                                 ColBack :: wx:wx_colour().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the background colour for the item.


.RE
.B
\fBsetColumn(This, Col) -> ok\fR
\fB                   when This :: wxListItem(), Col :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the zero-based column.

.PP
Meaningful only in report mode.


.RE
.B
\fBsetFont(This, Font) -> ok\fR
\fB                 when This :: wxListItem(), Font :: wxFont:wxFont().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the font for the item.


.RE
.B
\fBsetId(This, Id) -> ok when This :: wxListItem(), Id :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the zero-based item position.


.RE
.B
\fBsetImage(This, Image) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxListItem(), Image :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the zero-based index of the image associated with the item into the image list.


.RE
.B
\fBsetMask(This, Mask) -> ok\fR
\fB                 when This :: wxListItem(), Mask :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the mask of valid fields.

.PP
See \fIgetMask/1\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBsetState(This, State) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxListItem(), State :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the item state flags (note that the valid state flags are influenced by the value of the state mask, see \fIsetStateMask/2\fR).

.PP
See \fIgetState/1\fR for valid flag values.


.RE
.B
\fBsetStateMask(This, StateMask) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxListItem(), StateMask :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the bitmask that is used to determine which of the state flags are to be set.

.PP
See also \fIsetState/2\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBsetText(This, Text) -> ok\fR
\fB                 when This :: wxListItem(), Text :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the text label for the item.


.RE
.B
\fBsetTextColour(This, ColText) -> ok\fR
\fB                       when\fR
\fB                           This :: wxListItem(),\fR
\fB                           ColText :: wx:wx_colour().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the text colour for the item.


.RE
.B
\fBsetWidth(This, Width) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxListItem(), Width :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Meaningful only for column headers in report mode.

.PP
Sets the column width.


.RE
